    "department": "Legal",
    "description": "We believe conversations will become the #1 way to shop.\n\nAt Gorgias, we’re building the platform that makes this real: a unified AI agent that sells, supports, and re-engages customers across the entire journey. Conversational Commerce is the future of ecommerce, and we’re leading that shift.\n\nOur mission is to turn every interaction between a brand and its customers into a relationship: personal, seamless, and intelligent. By combining deep product expertise with the latest in AI, we’re making shopping feel more natural, human, and connected than ever before.\n\nTo win, we focus relentlessly on:\n\n - Quality: conversations that feel authentic and on-brand.\n\n - Experience: effortless shopping from chat to checkout.\n\n - Re-engagement: personal, 1-1 dialogue instead of noisy marketing.\n\nThe opportunity is massive. As AI reshapes how people buy, Gorgias is building the foundation for the next decade of ecommerce, where every brand has its own intelligent agent and every customer feels understood.\n\nJoin us to make Conversational Commerce real.\n\nThis is a temporary contract position running from June 2026 to December 2026.\n\n\nABOUT THE TEAM\n\nGorgias's Legal team is a 2-person AI-first function built for the pace of a scaling SaaS company. Our team mission is to empower our teams by providing legal guidance on topics including contracts, security, and privacy to better support business growth. We’re here to help protect Gorgias and give pro-active legal advices on legal issues and risks\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nMost legal teams in SaaS are still built for a world that no longer exists — one where value comes from volume, and speed is the bottleneck. We're building something different.\n\nAs Legal Counsel at Gorgias, you'll be the legal brain behind our commercial engine: part deal expert, part coach to sales and finance, part architect of the systems that make it all scale. This is an L3 role based in Toronto (hybrid), supporting our commercial motion and procurement process.\n\nYou'll work directly with our Head of Legal, owning the commercial legal function end-to-end as we scale.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Own end-to-end negotiation of commercial agreements: SaaS subscription agreements, MSAs, order forms, DPAs.\n\n - Be the primary legal point of contact for the sales team — coaching reps on deal risks, unblocking negotiations, and setting clear fallback positions\n\n - Build, maintain, and continuously improve our contract playbook and standard template suite\n\n - Manage and improve AI-assisted contract workflows (Claude, ChatGpt)\n\n - Partner with Finance and RevOps on deal structuring, billing terms, and revenue recognition edge cases\n\n - Handle vendor and inbound technology agreements, including SaaS and data processor relationships\n\n - Identify patterns across the deal portfolio and translate them into policy, training, or product input\n\n - Support general commercial legal work as the team scales\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\nMust Haves\n\n - 3-4 years of commercial legal experience, in-house at a SaaS or tech company, or in tech-focused private practice\n\n - Startup or scale-up experience: you've built or improved a process, not just executed within one\n\n - Exposure to US market commercial deals — you understand how US enterprise procurement works\n\n - Comfortable with ambiguity; you close deals, you don't just flag risk\n\n - Strong written communication — your redlines are tight, your emails move things forward\n\n - Genuine curiosity about AI tools and a willingness to work with AI.\n\nNice to Haves\n\n - Licensed in both Canada and a US state (dual bar is a strong plus)\n\n - Experience with AI-assisted contract review tools\n\n\nWHAT GOOD LOOKS LIKE AT 6 MONTHS\n\n - Contract turnaround time: \u003c 2 business days for standard MSAs\n\n - Playbook coverage: 90%+ of common commercial scenarios documented\n\n - Escalations to outside counsel: \u003c 10% of matters\n\n - AI routing accuracy: \u003c 5% rerouting rate on AI-handled contracts\n\nAI at Gorgias\nAt Gorgias, AI is a natural extension of how we work and build. Our teams use it every day to research, write, analyze, code, and craft better customer experiences. Everyone has access to premium AI tools (ChatGPT, Claude, Granola \u0026 others) and an annual L\u0026D budget to explore new ones.\n\nThe real magic happens when we share what we learn. Our #powerup Slack channel is a digital petri dish of new tools and workflows, and each team has AI champions who showcase fresh ideas during weekly company-wide standups, now practically AI demo sessions.\n\nWe see AI not as a replacement for creativity or empathy, but as a multiplier, helping us move faster, think deeper, and serve customers better.\n\nAI use in Recruiting at Gorgias\nBy submitting your application, you agree that Gorgias may collect and process your personal data for recruiting, workforce planning, and related purposes. For more information about how we process your data and your rights, please refer to our Applicant Privacy Policy https://www.gorgias.com/legal/applicant-privacy-policy.\n\nDiversity \u0026 Inclusion at Gorgias\nWe’re committed to creating an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives because diverse teams drive innovation and better decision-making.\n\nIf you need accommodations during the application or interview process, please contact us at accommodation@gorgias.com.",
